title: Bonnie Raitt 2016-04-23 mk4 Oakland flac16
description:
Here is a very nice digital recording from Bonnie Raitt's performance last week. 

Check my account for more classic bootlegs.

Please enjoy, share with friends and please seed :)

Bonnie Raitt
Fox Theater
Oakland, Ca
April 23,2016 


Recorded by Daspyknows 
Orchestra Pit 6th row a few seats off dead center

Schoeps MK4/NBox Platinum Tascam DR-2D 24 Bit 48K 


Processed using Soundforge 11, resample, to 16bit 44.1K 
TLH to convert to Flac 


Master 2016.18 


SETLIST-

01. Need You Tonight
02. Used To Rule The World
03. I Knew
04. Undone
05. Shakin' Shakin' Shakes
06. Right Down The Line
07. Round And Round
08. I Feel The Same
09. Women Be Wise
10. Hear Me Lord
11. Something To Talk About
12. The Comin' Round Is Going Through
13. Angel From Montgomery
14. Don't Answer The Door
15. Gypsy In Me
16. Good Man, Good Woman
17. What You're Doin' To Me
18. Crowd/Talk
19. I Can't Make You Love Me
20. Not The Only One
21. Burning Down The House
22. Your Sweet And Shiny Eyes 

First show back after being on the road and I forgot how much I like 
hometown shows.  Picked up my seats at will call.  Everything was easy.
During opening act The California Honeydrops I knew the sound was spot
on.  I also knew there was a loudmouth directly behind me. Luckily she
was behind me because she can be heard at at few points thinking she was 
conversing with Bonnie or hacking up a lung.  This was one of the best
Bonnie sets I have seen.  New setlist mixed with both new and old.  A few
real gems.  Band was tight and Bonnie was having fun.  Great sound and 
performance.  Enjoy.  Need help with setlist.  It was either get it posted
without a list today or wait a week until I got around to figuring it out.


Just the basic taper requests here and please no vitriol: 
Don't be an ass by selling this or using it in a video that is sold 
Don't modify the info file 
Don't remaster and/or post on other sites that are not 100% free 
If shared keep info file intact but create a second file with any changes 
Don't convert to lossy formats except for personal use 
Do support the artists
